        *        *
 
Some great teachers, especially of the Adwaita philoso=
phy, are like the great cricket batsman in the above analogy. They tell you=
 what is obvious and natural to *them*. Their words are very inspiring.
 
S=
ome other teachers fine-tune their message for an audience. They show a rea=
l path (instead of a lofty target) using which one can start making progres=
s. One may or may not reach a supreme state anytime soon, but one will star=
t making progress.
 
*        *        *
 
Different spiritual teachers com=
e for different purposes. The role played by each one is important in its o=
wn right. Ramana maharshi was undoubtedly a great master. However, when it =
comes to the second category of teachers I mentioned above, one name that s=
trikes to me instantly is that of Ramakrishna Paramahamsa. He was a master =
at fine-tuning his message for the individual. While most great masters wer=
e adepts in one path (jnaana yoga or bhakti yoga or karma yoga or raja yoga=
), he was unique in that he experienced the supreme through each path and w=
as equally comfortable guiding people in jnaana, vedanta, Raama bhakti, Kri=
shna bhakti, Kaali bhakti, Shiva bhakti, karma yoga, service, hatha yoga, t=
antra etc, having experienced all. He even did smashana sadhanas, Islamic s=
adhanas and experienced Jesus Christ. He is a unique teacher in the last fe=
w millennia. Many other masters take disciples on the path they walked. Hav=
ing walked all paths to the summit, Ramakrishna guided disciples on differe=
nt paths based on their aptitude.
 
*        *        *
 
Though upanishads=
 and Bhagavad Gita are teaching Adwaita clearly, some great masters came in=
 the last few millennia who taught variations in the Upanishadic philosophy=
 veering towards duality to various degrees. I think this happened for a pu=
rpose. As true Adwaita as taught by Upanishads and Bhagavad Gita becomes mo=
re and more inappropriate and difficult for the masses, a simpler message t=
hat they can understand and that can guide their spiritual lives is needed.=
 I think the coming of various masters who taught different philosophies is=
 for that reason.
 
