The title of the mail was "Fearle=
ssness Comes In The Supreme State Of Non-duality". However, the question is=
: Does non-duality bring fearlessness or vice versa?
 
A realization of non=
-dual Self may suddenly happen oneday for some rare persons. For most, it h=
appens as a result of sadhana done over many years/lives. Thus, qualities l=
ike dispassion, fearlessness (which are associated with the supreme state) =
need to be cultivated actively. As they become more and more perfected, one=
 gets closer and closer to Self-realization.
 
Suppose one sees a beautiful=
/ugly object (or a desirable/undesirable object). When one feels attraction=
/aversion, one should remind oneself "all is god (Self). There is no need f=
or feeling attraction/aversion towards anything." When one feels fear, one =
should remind oneself "all is god (Self). There is no need for be afraid of=
 *anything*". As one practices this, one's dispassion and fearlessness incr=
ease. Incidents of delusion becomes smaller and less frequent. Eventually, =
one overcomes.
 
But the tricky part is that one needs to perform the actio=
ns one is meant to perform and work out the kaarmik debts, before one reali=
zes Self. It is very difficult to perform actions without feeling even smal=
l amounts of attachment, attraction, aversion, passion, fear etc.
 
A simpl=
e formula is: Give all you can and expect nothing (and accept whatever you =
get) in return. In the beginning, any attraction/aversion/anxiety/fear you =
feel should be with regard to what are giving to others and not with regard=
 to what you are expecting from others.
 
