It is all e=
asy to write and read theory. The problem comes when one is tested in real =
life. For example, I choked when eating something once when I was alone and=
 could not breathe. I became anxious and it made it worse. Suddenly, the th=
ought came to me "what are you afraid of? Death? This will mostly result in=
 a little suffering for a couple of minutes and no more. EVEN IF it results=
 in death, what is the big deal? Jaatasya dhruvam mrityuh (each being who i=
s born is sure of deatth). Is there anything I wanted to do and could not d=
o? Well, there may be, but someone else can do it. Why should only Narasimh=
a do it? World will run perfectly fine even if I am not here. If I indeed d=
ie now, why don't I meditate and focus my mind on god, instead of focusing =
on my life and getting anxious?" I relaxed and meditated for a few minutes =
with Gayatri mantra. My anxiety went away and I felt nice after a while.
 
=
As one detects and actively suppresses undesirable thoughts more and more, =
such thoughts will become less and less frequent and eventually be suppress=
ed by the mind even in the seed/formatory state. Later, causes of those see=
ds themselves will be wiped out from the sub-conscious mind. This is how co=
nditioning of the mind is slowly overcome. It is certainly a long process f=
or most of us, but one loses nothing by starting and trying to make progres=
s. Sadhanas like homam and japam aid one in this.
 
Please note that even R=
amana maharshi and Ramakrishna Paramahamsa did intense sadhana for many yea=
rs, before they could reach the supreme state. No matter who you are, some =
sadhana is needed.
 
